League leaders, Rivers United, continue their fine form on Sunday in one of the week 17 games of the Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) with a 2-0 win over the visiting Shooting Stars of Ibadan at the Yakubu Gowon Stadium in Port Harcourt. A brace from Joseph Onoja in the eighth and twenty-fifth minute made the difference for the Pride of Rivers who are well on course to go all the way if they can maintain consistency. On the strength of the result, the former CAF Champions League campaigners consolidated their stay atop the twenty-team table with thirty-eight points from seventeen games. Excitement As 3SC Back In ‘Premiership’ NPFL: Akwa United Grabs Trophy As It Trashes Mountain Of Fire To… Plateau United remain second while Remo Stars regained the third spot after they dispatched Sunshine Stars 3-0 in Remo, Ogun State. In the results of other matches decided on Sunday, two times African champions, Enyimba International of Aba, lost 2-0 to the home side, Dakkada FC, in Uyo, while their neighbours, Abia Warriors of Umuahia could only manage a goalless affair with the visiting Akwa United at the Okigwe Township Stadium, their adopted home ground. In Lagos, the Mountain of Fire and Miracles Ministries (MFM) Football Club failed to make their home count as they fell once again but this time to the Afonja Warriors, Kwara United, 2-1. In Jos, Plateau United left it late to pip Katsina United 1-0, even as Wikki Tourists, playing at their home, also got better of Lobi Stars with the same margin. Playing at the Ahmadu Bello Stadium in Kaduna as their home ground, Kano Pillars whipped Nasarawa United 2-0.